sentences: Anthony  Ulysses Thompson, Jr. (September 2, 1975 – June 1, 2007) was an American singer–songwriter.
Thompson was best known as the lead vocalist of the American R&B quintet Hi-Five, which had hit singles such as "I Like the Way (The Kissing Game)" and "I Can't Wait Another Minute".
After the group disbanded in 1994, Thompson found solo success the following year with his debut album Sexsational in 1995.

Taking the name Hi-Five, the group signed with Jive Records in 1989.
